# useColorModeValue

`useColorModeValue` is a React hook used to change any value or style based on the color mode. It takes 2 arguments: the value in light mode, and the value in dark mode.

## Import

```jsx live=false
import { useColorModeValue } from '@totejs/uikit';
```

## Usage

```jsx live=false
// Here's the signature
const value = useColorModeValue(lightModeValue, darkModeValue);
```

```jsx
function StyleColorMode() {
  const { toggleColorMode } = useColorMode();

  const bg = useColorModeValue('scene.danger.normal', 'scene.success.normal');
  const color = useColorModeValue('white', 'red');

  return (
    <>
      <Box mb={16} bg={bg} color={color}>
        This box's style will change based on the color mode.
      </Box>
      <Button onClick={toggleColorMode}>Toggle Mode</Button>
    </>
  );
}
```

